title: SPI Subform 3
description: Safety Planning Intervention Subform 3 - Information Only (Low Risk)

item.text: Provide psychoeducation and describe when to seek help

Example dialogue #1
If you are feeling suicidal, you might be scared or confused by these feelings. But you are not alone. Many people think about suicide at some point in their lifetime.

Example dialogue #2
You might be feeling so upset, and in pain that you believe these feelings will never end. But it's important to remember that they cannot and will not last. Like all feelings, these ones will pass.
Review the Crisis Curve with the client. Explain how suicidal crises change over time.

If you ever start to have thoughts of hurting yourself, you can:
  •  Reach out to someone you trust for help
  •  Contact your primary or mental health care provider and make an appointment
  •  Call 988
